California v. United States. May 12, 1941. Messrs. Burton Smith, John L. McNab, and Edw. D. Hays for plaintiff. Per Curiam:

The motion for leave tó file complaint is denied. Kansas v. United States, 204 U. S. 331; Williams v. United States, 289 U. S. 553, 573; Principality of Monaco v. Mississippi, 292 U. S. 313, 321.
